                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.348 Z 4/47: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-01T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1923—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 1—10:24 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>113. Department’s unnumbered instructions September 18th last. Minister of
                    Foreign Affairs states Belgian Government will grant desired permission for
                    passage of airship mentioned over Belgian territory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
